Durban - #FeesMustFall activist, Bonginkosi Khanyile, will have to wait until January 28, 2019, to know how many years - if any - he will spend behind bars. 
Khanyile was due to be sentenced at the Durban Magistrate's Court today however, the matter was postponed due to incomplete reports. 

Khanyile pleaded guilty to four charges including public violence relating to #FeesMustFall protests at the Durban University of Technology in September 2016.
